snippet.textDisplay:
To all those fellow Indians who are peddling their love here and saying that we are but a single nation and represent same culture, I beg to differ with you, guys. Yes, we've similarities; yes, our culture shares some familiar features; and yes, our appearances may seem same, to some extent,  BUT, with all due respect, we both are are different nations. We have different religious beliefs, and many other things for that matter, and it is unfair to criticize the separation of our lands. We had been given fair chances and we sucked living together.
